Hon\f2\rquote\f0 ble Speaker,\par
I present the Budget for the year 2021-2022.\par
Introduction\par
1. Honourable Speaker, the preparation of this Budget was undertaken in circumstances like never before. We knew of calamities that have affected a country or a region within a country, but what we have endured with COVID-19 through 2020 is sui generis.\par
2. When I presented the Budget 2020-21, we could not have imagined that the global economy, already in throes of a slowdown, would be pushed into an unprecedented contraction.\par
3. We could not have also imagined then that our people as those in other countries would have to endure the loss of near and dear ones and suffer hardships brought about due to a health crisis.\par
4. The risk of not having a lockdown was far too high. Within 48 hours of declaring a three-week-long complete lockdown, the Prime Minister announced the Pradhan Mantri Garib Kalyan Yojana, valued at `2.76 lakh crores \f2\endash  this provided, free food grain to 800 million people, free cooking\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 gas for 80 million families for months, and cash directly to over 400 million\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 farmers, women, elderly, the poor and the needy.\par
5. Even as a large section of citizens stayed home, milk, vegetable, and\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 fruit-suppliers, health and sanitary workers, truck drivers, railways and\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 public transport workers, bank employees, electricity workers, our\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 annadatas, police, firemen, and the armed forces, all had to go about their\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 work as normal, but with the additional anxiety of the virus hanging over\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 them. We recognise this, and I think I speak on behalf of everybody in this\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 august House, when I express my heartfelt gratitude to these men and\par
women, for how they were able to carry out their work and duty, to provide\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 for the nation\rquote s basics, over those crucial months.\par
6. Speaker Sir, for public good, Honourable Members of Parliament\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 and Members of Legislative Assemblies too offered their salaries.\par
7. In May 2020, the government announced the AtmaNirbhar Bharat\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 package (ANB 1.0). To sustain the recovery, further into the year, we also\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 rolled out two more AtmaNirbhar Bharat packages (ANB 2.0 and ANB 3.0).\par
Total financial impact of all AtmaNirbhar Bharat packages including\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 measures taken by RBI was estimated to about `27.1 lakh crores which\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 amounts to more than 13% of GDP.\par
8. As a government, we kept a watch on the situation and were\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 proactive in our responses. The government, led by the Prime Minister,\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 stretched its resources to deliver for most vulnerable sections of our society\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9\endash  the poorest of the poor, the Dalits, Tribals, the elderly, the migrant\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 workers, and our children. The PMGKY, the three ANB packages, and\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 announcements made later were like five mini-budgets in themselves.\par
9. The AtmaNirbhar Packages accelerated our pace of structural\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 reforms. Redefinition of MSMEs, Commercialisation of the Mineral Sector,\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 Agriculture and Labour Reforms, Privatisation of Public Sector Undertakings,\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 One Nation One Ration Card, and Production Linked Incentive Schemes are\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 some of the notable reforms carried out during this period. Faceless\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 Income Tax Assessment, DBT and Financial Inclusion are the others.\par
10. Today, India has two vaccines available, and has begun medically\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 safeguarding not only her own citizens against COVID-19, but also those of\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 100 or more countries. It is added comfort to know that two or more\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 vaccines are also expected soon.\par
11. Honourable Prime Minister launched the vaccination drive by\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 crediting and thanking our scientists. We are ever grateful for the strength\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 and rigour of their efforts.\par
12. Having said that, we are all reminded time and again that our fight\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 against COVID-19 continues into 2021.\par
13. Now, just as it had happened after the two World Wars, there are\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 signs that the political, economic, and strategic relations in the post COVID\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 world are changing. This moment in history is the dawn of a new era \endash  one\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 in which India is well-poised to truly be the land of promise and hope.\par
''Faith is the bird that feels the light and sings when the dawn is still dark''.\par
-Rabindranath Tagore\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 (Fireflies \endash  A Collection of Aphorisms)\par
14. In this spirit, I can\rquote t help but recall the joy that we, as a cricket-loving\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 nation, felt after Team India\rquote s recent spectacular success in Australia. It has\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 reminded us of all the qualities that we as a people, particularly our youth,\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 epitomise of having abundant promise and the unsuppressed thirst to\par
perform and succeed.\par
15. Today, data shows that India now has one of the lowest death rate\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 of 112 per million population and one of the lowest active cases of about\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 130 per million. This has laid the foundation to the revival we are seeing\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 now in the economy.\par
16. This Budget will be the first of this new decade. This Budget will also\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 be a digital Budget and that has happened with all your support.\par
17. So far, only three times has a Budget followed a contraction in the\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 economy. All such contractions were as a result of situations typical to\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 India. This time, the contraction in our economy is due to a global\par
pandemic, just like in several other countries.\par
18. Having said that, I want to confidently state that our Government is\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 fully prepared to support and facilitate the economy\rquote s reset. This Budget\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 provides every opportunity for our economy to raise and capture the pace\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 that it needs for sustainable growth.\par
19. 2021 is the year of many important milestones for our history. I\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 mention a few of these: It is the 75th year of Independence; 60 years of\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 Goa\rquote s accession to India; 50 years of the 1971 India-Pakistan War; it will be the year of the 8th Census of Independent India; it will also be India\rquote s turn\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 at the BRICS Presidency; the year for our Chandrayaan-3 Mission; and the\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 Haridwar Maha Kumbh.\par
20. Honourable Speaker, before I commence Part A of the Budget, I\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 want to take a moment to acknowledge how isolating and distancing\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 seemed like insurmountable challenges for a country like ours that has\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 people coming together in times of crises. It hurt us in many ways. I bow my\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 head in respect to every citizen, for the endurance shown in facing what\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 was an undeniably a tough year for all our physical and mental well-being.\par
\par
\b PART A\par
\b0 21. In Part A, I wish to lay a vision for AtmaNirbhar Bharat.\par
22. AtmaNirbharta is not a new idea. Ancient India was largely selfreliant, and equally, a business\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 epicentre of the world.\par
23. AtmaNirbhar Bharat is an expression of 130 crores Indians who have\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 full confidence in their capabilities and skills.\par
24. We are already part of International groupings such as the G20 and\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 BRICS. The Coalition for Disaster Resilient Infrastructure and the\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 International Solar alliance are realities today due to India\rquote s efforts.\par
25. The proposals in Part A will further strengthen the sankalp of Nation\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 First, Doubling Farmer\rquote s Income, Strong Infrastructure, Healthy India, Good\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 Governance, Opportunities for Youth, Education for All, Women\par
Empowerment, and Inclusive Development, among others.\par
26. Additionally, also on the path to fast-implementation are the 13\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 promises we had made in the Budget of 2015-16 which were to materialise\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 during the Amrut Mahotsav of 2022, on the 75th year of our \f0\lang2057 I\f2\lang9 ndependence.\f0\lang2057  \f2\lang9 They too resonate with this vision of AtmaNirbharta.\par
27. The Budget proposals for 2021-2022 rest on 6 pillars.\par
i. Health and Wellbeing\par
ii. Physical & Financial Capital, and Infrastructure\par
iii. Inclusive Development for Aspirational India\par
